704962f-b.title: Brooklyn: Highland Park.
704962f-b.text:
Highland Park (Queens-Brooklyn):  Shown are several early views of the park, part of which is in Queens and part in Brooklyn.  Views 1 and 2 show the Ridgewood Reservoir, picnic grounds and National Cemetery (view 2).  The reservoir is in Queens; the cemetery in Brooklyn.  View 3 shows the fence aroudn the reservoir and the Interborough Parkway (left).

Wilberforce Eames Collection
1916
Views 1-4

704961f-a.title: Brooklyn: Highland Park.
704961f-a.text:
Highland Park: a general view south, showing Jamaica Ave., south side, between Narwick and Linwood Streets. On the north side of the Ave., from the extreme left to the extreme right, are the Stoothoff and Schenck homes.

About 1920.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
